        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                    <p><img src="https://github.com/wvrossem/cautious-succotash/media/posts/1/Screenshot-2026-03-16-at-12-21-59-Sadaritagi-sadaritagi-on-Scratch.png" class="type:primaryImage" alt="" /></p>
                <h2 data-path-to-node="5">🚀 Sadaritagi 사다리타기</h2>
<p data-path-to-node="6"><strong data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="0">Date: </strong>June 2025</p>
<p data-path-to-node="6"><strong data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="21">Coding Language:</strong> Scratch</p>
<h3 data-path-to-node="8">🎮 About My Project</h3>
<p data-path-to-node="9">Work in progress version of the Korean Sadaritagi (사다리타기 "ladder climbing") game. It's kind of game to create random pairings. In this version a cat randomly starts at one of the four legs and will randomly end up at one of the four end points due to the randomly placed ladder legs.<br><br>It is also known in Japanese as Amidakuji (阿弥陀籤; "Amida lottery") and in Chinese as Guijiaotu (Chinese: 鬼腳圖,  "ghost leg diagram"). </p>
<h3 data-path-to-node="11">🧩 How It Works (The Logic)</h3>
<p data-path-to-node="13,0,0">The code draws the ladders by drawing the vertical lines and randomly placed horizontal lines to connect the different "legs".</p>
<p data-path-to-node="13,0,0">It cat moves downwards and uses the green and purple dots on the connecting legs to move between the legs.</p>
<h3 data-path-to-node="14">🐞 What I Want to Improve</h3>
<p data-path-to-node="15">The cat should make a combination for each starting and ending position.</p>
<h3 data-path-to-node="16,0,0">🌟 Try It Out!</h3>
